Chef's Delight is a productivity platform built for personal chefs, solo operators, and culinary consultants. It puts six business tools in one dashboard — so a chef can spend more time cooking and less time managing scattered apps.

## What We Built

**Blog with AI Q&A** — Chefs publish recipes, techniques, and stories. Visitors can ask the AI assistant questions about any post and get helpful answers based on the chef's own content.

**Client Management** — Track clients, projects, and invoices. Payments through Stripe, automatic invoice numbering, and a full history of every engagement.

**Booking System** — Private dinners, cooking classes, meal prep, catering consultations — each with pricing and duration. Customers book online, get confirmation emails, and receive reminders before their appointment. The AI booking assistant helps visitors choose the right service.

**Online Store** — Sell cookbooks, kitchen gear, spice blends, and merchandise. Product catalog with inventory tracking, sale pricing, and Stripe checkout. The AI recommends products based on what visitors are looking for.

**Social Media** — Connect Instagram, Facebook, and LinkedIn. Schedule posts across platforms with a visual content calendar and track engagement.

**Newsletter** — Subscribers sign up with AI-powered interest discovery — the system learns what each person cares about and personalizes the content they receive.

## How We Approached It

We chose a tech stack based on what would perform best and cost the least to run — a decision validated by our agent governance review. The result is a fast, reliable app that handles everything without expensive monthly software subscriptions.

The marketing site was designed with a warm, culinary brand identity — distinct typography, an earth-tone color palette, and food photography throughout. It doesn't look like a tech product; it looks like something a chef would be proud to share with clients.

Instead of a generic chat bubble, the AI appears naturally on each page: a search bar on the homepage ("What are you in the mood for?"), and inline chat sections on the blog, store, and booking pages with contextual suggestions. It feels like asking a knowledgeable friend, not talking to a bot.

## Agent Governance Review

Every project we build goes through our agent governance review — a structured evaluation by specialized AI agents that check the project from multiple angles:

- **Client alignment** scored **9.3/10** — the app exceeded what was requested on 7 of 8 features
- **End-user experience** scored **8.5/10** — the AI assistants were the standout, making the site feel premium and helpful
- **Stack evaluation** confirmed the technology choices were **optimal for performance and cost** — the right tools for the job, nothing over-engineered
- **Technical quality** confirmed solid foundations — well-tested, well-structured, and ready for future growth

## The Result

A chef can now manage their entire online presence from one place: publish a blog post in the morning, check their bookings over lunch, update the store in the afternoon, and schedule social media posts for the week — all without switching between five different apps. And their customers get a beautiful, AI-assisted experience that makes browsing, booking, and shopping feel effortless.
